Josh Meekings deliberately handled the ball during Inverness's 3-2 Scottish Cup semi-final victory against Celtic . 
 Meekings escaped punishment for the act during the game . 
 In the aftermath of the 3-2 extra-time win, Meekings admitted he was fortunate not to have conceded a penalty and been red-carded . 
 On Thursday, the Inverness defender was cleared to play in the Scottish Cup Final against Falkirk on May 30 . 
 